The Nigeria Police High Command has dispelled rumours and claims that terrorists have occupied Muhammadu Buhari Police estate located in Badagry, Lagos.
   
Police’s spokesperson, Chief Superintendent of Police (CSP), Muyiwa Adejobi, who dispelled the rumour  in a statement yesterday, noting that the estate is fully occupied by police officers and members of other security agencies.
 
He said: “The police wish to state categorically that the Muhammadu Buhari estate situated at Agemowo, Badagry, Lagos State, is the property of the Nigeria Police Cooperative Multipurpose Society and by extension, the Nigeria Police Force. 